			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">How about we drop CD as the Sorcerer Realm ability and they implement one like this:
<br />
Name:  Shared Fate
<br />
Cost:  14 points
<br />
Effect:  Links you and your pet together.  All damage done to either you or your pet is shared as if you shared the same hit point pool (Use the larger of the two, not combine them).  Killing one also kills the other.  Makes pet immune to Sever the Tether.
<br />

<br />
This would allow the Sorcerer more survivability and a way to counter STT.  Unlike the Necro, we can still be hit and interrupted, CC'd individually, etc.  This would also bring our pets back as a threat, where as now they just charge past the pet and kill us or STT it and the pet kills us.  
<br />

<br />
Once upon a time, it was a risk to attack a Sorcerer with a pet, because after you killed him, his pet would hunt you down.  While that will never happen again, this will atleast make others have to acknowledge the pet.
<br />

<br />
This would also take some RvRing to bring us up to par, atleast as far as tanks, as most people these days will have no problem soloing a yellow this shouldnt be overpowering.  The fact that we have no AF to speak of means they can still focus on us to take us out faster than if they focus on pet first.
<br />

<br />
Whats your thoughts?
<br />

<br />
Shyann Silvermane
<br />
High Sorcerer of Igraine
<br />
Guardian Council Leader</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
