			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I do not think those abilities will help survivability at all really...
<br />
They sound cool, but overall, they will not make much impact. I mean even with 25% more life, we will die in two seconds instead of one and a half. With 75% more life you might actually live long enough to cast something, but you will still get interupted - and if you do cast something you will do crap damage. No, it will just prolong the inevitable...
<br />

<br />
The pooling of the life, again sounds cool, but will not make a difference in the end.
<br />

<br />
The MAIN problem I think we have is our inability to get out of melee once engaged. More life will not help this, no matter how you buff, pool or whatever. 
<br />

<br />
I have two ideas that I think would solve the survivability problem, or at least greatly enhance it. Just one alone would be ebough, for both together would be to much, (but I would take that is I could get it..) <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
1.) Fix confusion to work in RvR - For the duration of the spell let the direction controls of the target player change randomly every 2 seconds and have him loose target every 4 seconds (with /stick and /follow disabled during the duration). Same type of immunity timers would apply as with mez.
<br />

<br />
2. a 2 second ( dare I say instant??) short range random teleport such as Shadow Step or Yonder from EQ. I think a 3 minute recast timer would be fair.
<br />

<br />
Either one of these would help. The both just have one major problem... They would also greatly maximize our offensive potential. To balance this, I suggest that there be a 20 second recast timer for all damage spells after one of the above was cast. That would stop us from abusing it.
<br />

<br />
So, what do you yll think of those ideas?
<br />

<br />
Hehe, can I apply for TL position now? <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Quenton aKa Amiga, Lancelot</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
