			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quenton wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I do not think those abilities will help survivability at all really...
<br />
They sound cool, but overall, they will not make much impact. I mean even with 25% more life, we will die in two seconds instead of one and a half. With 75% more life you might actually live long enough to cast something, but you will still get interupted - and if you do cast something you will do crap damage. No, it will just prolong the inevitable...
<br />

<br />
The pooling of the life, again sounds cool, but will not make a difference in the end.
<br />

<br />
The MAIN problem I think we have is our inability to get out of melee once engaged. More life will not help this, no matter how you buff, pool or whatever. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I agree Quenton.  The point of it was to help the sorc in a group.  That extra second might be enuff for your tank to land a slam, or for another caster to stun/root the guy on you.  May also help you recieve heals.
<br />
If you and the pet is buffed, that's more life, and with group heals, good also.
<br />

<br />
I think the sorcerer survivability is rather special.  I mean, all caster are dead as soon as they are melee, we ain't special in that way.  Cloth = weak, we can't expect to tank much.  
<br />
No, the problem is, even in a WINNING situation, let's say a 8 vs 8, you will win, with only one guy dead: the sorc.  First man down, no RPs.  
<br />
So i figured, well, maybe these extra seconds would help get a bit more RPs...  The point is not to cast more, just to live more.
<br />

<br />
Your confusion idea sound very strong to me, i mean, that's an insta win Vs any tank in 1 vs 1.  Or stealthers.   QC mez, get distance, confuse, sick pet, laugh.
<br />

<br />
Another of my idea adress the actual cause of our survival issue.  Why do we die more then wizzards, or cabby or theurgist?   Because we cast first.  A caby can wait until the combat starts and cast DoT.  The wizz wil stay back, then run in and PBAoE.
<br />

<br />
The sorc, with the bolt mez, will be the first to cast.  You initiate aggression.  First to AoE = auto-targeted by all.  That means...  Mez... get spirit master pet on you, that purging zerker on you, that skald that resisted on you, and that RM that was on the verge of mez and unmezz after 2 sec will bolt.  Boum bada Boum.  Dead sorc.
<br />

<br />
That is saddly DAoC today.  Who needs skills with /face /stick /last attacker and auto-targeting...  
<br />

<br />
Solution?  Change CD for this RA:
<br />

<br />
Phase out, cost 10, recast 7 minute (like moose/badger modes)  Insta cast, uses 25% mana.
<br />
Effect: Sorcerer phases out (becomes untargetable and invisible) for 3 sec.  
<br />

<br />
This would act exaclty like stealth does: as you phase out, you actually get clear of everyone's targeting system.  
<br />
Sound a bit too good.... lol, ok maybe 10 minute timer <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
